NLquery:
For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used 
version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions 
have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT t.sid, t.version
FROM (
    SELECT
        bm.sid,
        bm.version,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY bm.sid
            ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM BaseModels AS bm
    GROUP BY bm.sid, bm.version
) AS t
WHERE t.rn = 1;

NLquery:
Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model
 built by the agent creator user_iuwrh
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT i.sid
FROM InternetService i
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM BaseModel b
    WHERE b.creator = 'user_iuwrh'
      AND NOT EXISTS (
          SELECT 1
          FROM ModelInternetService mis
          WHERE mis.base_model_id = b.id
            AND mis.sid = i.sid
      )
);

NLquery:
For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used
 version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions 
have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt:
Translate this natural language query into SQL:
SCHEMA:
QUERY:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT ms.sid,
       ms.version
FROM ModelServices ms
JOIN (
    SELECT sid,
           version,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
               PARTITION BY sid
               ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
           ) AS rn
    FROM ModelServices
    GROUP BY sid, version
) ranked
  ON ranked.sid = ms.sid
 AND ranked.version = ms.version
WHERE ranked.rn = 1;

NLquery:
Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model
 built by the agent creator user_iuwrh
prompt:
Translate this natural language query into SQL:
SCHEMA:
QUERY:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT ms.sid
FROM Users u
JOIN AgentCreator ac ON ac.uid = u.uid
JOIN BaseModel bm ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid
JOIN ModelServices ms ON ms.bmid = bm.bmid
WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh'
GROUP BY ms.sid
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT bm.bmid) =
       (
         SELECT COUNT(*)
         FROM Users u2
         JOIN AgentCreator ac2 ON ac2.uid = u2.uid
         JOIN BaseModel bm2 ON bm2.creator_uid = ac2.uid
         WHERE u2.username = 'user_iuwrh'
       );

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt:
Translate this natural language query into SQL:
SCHEMA:
QUERY:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT cm.mid
FROM CustomizedModel AS cm
LEFT JOIN ModelConfigurations AS mc
  ON cm.bmid = mc.bmid AND cm.mid = mc.mid
WHERE mc.mid IS NULL;

NLquery:
For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used 
version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions 
have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt:
You are a SQL expert. Achieve this NL2SQL task from 
the given natural language query and table schema:
SCHEMA:
QUERY:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT T1.sid, T1.version
FROM (
    SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS frequency,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
               PARTITION BY sid
               ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
           ) AS rn
    FROM ModelServices
    GROUP BY sid, version
) AS T1
WHERE T1.rn = 1;

NLquery:
Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model
 built by the agent creator user_iuwrh
prompt:
You are a SQL expert. Achieve this NL2SQL task from 
the given natural language query and table schema:
SCHEMA:
QUERY:
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT T3.sid
FROM BaseModel AS T1
INNER JOIN User AS U
  ON T1.creator_uid = U.uid
INNER JOIN ModelServices AS T3
  ON T1.bmid = T3.bmid
WHERE
  U.username = 'user_iuwrh'
GROUP BY
  T3.sid
HAVING
  COUNT(DISTINCT T1.bmid) = (
    SELECT
      COUNT(T4.bmid)
    FROM BaseModel AS T4
    INNER JOIN User AS U2
      ON T4.creator_uid = U2.uid
    WHERE
      U2.username = 'user_iuwrh'
);
